<subSubSection id="12E932B9FFB1982F0197ACCA7601FE7C" pageId="17" pageNumber="503" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5A4C6132FFB1982F0197ACCA7601FE7C" blockId="17.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFB1982F0197ACCA7211FF60" bold="true" box="[199,308,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFB1982F0012ACCA711DFF61" box="[322,568,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Cosmolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="17" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sejongi">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFB1982F0012ACCA711DFF61" box="[322,568,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">Cosmolaelaps sejongi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry id="22E421A2FFB1982F024FACCA70C8FF60" box="[799,1005,151,177]" name="South Korea" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">Republic of Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFB1982F02ABACCA77EFFF60" author="Keum, E. &amp; Jung, C. &amp; Joharchi, O." box="[1019,1226,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="503" pagination="485 - 505" refId="ref15495" refString="Keum, E., Jung, C. &amp; Joharchi, O. (2017) New species and new records of the family Laelapidae (Acari: Mesostigmata) from Republic of Korea. Zootaxa, 4353 (3), 485 - 505. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4353.3.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Keum 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFB1982F0518ACCA775CFF60" box="[1096,1145,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">et al</emphasis>
., 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). It has been found from soil around roots of an oak tree (
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFB1982F0368ACE67020FF04" author="Keum, E. &amp; Jung, C. &amp; Joharchi, O." box="[568,773,187,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="503" pagination="485 - 505" refId="ref15495" refString="Keum, E., Jung, C. &amp; Joharchi, O. (2017) New species and new records of the family Laelapidae (Acari: Mesostigmata) from Republic of Korea. Zootaxa, 4353 (3), 485 - 505. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4353.3.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Keum 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFB1982F03D5ACE67190FF04" box="[645,693,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">et al</emphasis>
., 2017
</bibRefCitation>
), and is now recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="22E421A2FFB1982F0549ACE67741FF04" box="[1049,1124,187,213]" name="Russia" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">Russia</collectingCountry>
for the first time, in the nest of 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFB1982F01E6AC82721AFF28" baseAuthorityName="Nylander" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[182,319,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbratus">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFB1982F01E6AC8273E3FF29" box="[182,198,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFB1982F0185AC82721AFF28" box="[213,319,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">umbratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our specimens agree well with the description given by 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFB1982F029DAC82778CFF28" author="Keum, E. &amp; Jung, C. &amp; Joharchi, O." box="[973,1193,223,249]" pageId="17" pageNumber="503" pagination="485 - 505" refId="ref15495" refString="Keum, E., Jung, C. &amp; Joharchi, O. (2017) New species and new records of the family Laelapidae (Acari: Mesostigmata) from Republic of Korea. Zootaxa, 4353 (3), 485 - 505. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4353.3.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Keum 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFB1982F054AAC827769FF28" box="[1050,1100,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
. The species is easily recognised by the distinctive shape of the post-anal seta (thickened, sparsely barbed and apically hook shaped), which is inserted on a small tubercle (
<figureCitation id="C2C87DB7FFB1982F031AAD7A71F5FE90" box="[586,720,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–49" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1406,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@16.[180,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 45–49. DIC micrographs of Cosmolaelaps sejongi Keum, Jung and Joharchi, female. 45, idiosoma in dorsal view; 46, idiosoma in ventral view; 47, general view of some opisthonotal setae; 48, sternal and genital shields; 49, general view of opisthogastric area." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530986/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">Figs 46, 49</figureCitation>
); dorsal shield setae thick and long, most setae long enough to reach well past the base of next posterior seta, and 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFB1982F03B4AD167027FEB4" box="[740,770,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">Z5</emphasis>
sparsely barbed, longer and thicker than 
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFB1982F058DAD1677DDFEB4" box="[1245,1272,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">J5</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C2C87DB7FFB1982F0459AD1676AAFEB4" box="[1289,1423,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–49" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1406,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@16.[180,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 45–49. DIC micrographs of Cosmolaelaps sejongi Keum, Jung and Joharchi, female. 45, idiosoma in dorsal view; 46, idiosoma in ventral view; 47, general view of some opisthonotal setae; 48, sternal and genital shields; 49, general view of opisthogastric area." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530986/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">Figs 45, 47</figureCitation>
); sternal setae short, not reaching base of following setae (
<figureCitation id="C2C87DB7FFB1982F024FAD327081FE58" box="[799,932,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–49" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1406,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-18@16.[180,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 45–49. DIC micrographs of Cosmolaelaps sejongi Keum, Jung and Joharchi, female. 45, idiosoma in dorsal view; 46, idiosoma in ventral view; 47, general view of some opisthonotal setae; 48, sternal and genital shields; 49, general view of opisthogastric area." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530986/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="503">Figs 46, 48</figureCitation>
); soft opisthogastric cuticle bearing 16 pairs setae, 
